indexToGrid-methods        package:NeuroImage        R Documentation

_c_o_n_v_e_r_t_s _a _1-_d_i_m_e_n_s_i_o_n_a_l _i_n_d_e_x _v_e_c_t_o_r _t_o _a _m_a_t_r_i_x _o_f _c_o_o_r_d_i_n_a_t_e_s

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     function to convert from 1-dimensional index coordinates to an
     n-dimensional coordinate representation.

_M_e_t_h_o_d_s:



     _x = "_B_r_a_i_n_S_l_i_c_e", _i_d_x = "_i_n_d_e_x" converts a 1-dimensional index
          vector to a two-column matrix of coordinates 

     _x = "_B_r_a_i_n_S_p_a_c_e", _i_d_x = "_i_n_d_e_x" converts a 1-dimensional index
          vector to a n-column matrix of coordinates  

     _x = "_B_r_a_i_n_V_o_l_u_m_e", _i_d_x = "_i_n_d_e_x" converts a 1-dimensional index
          vector to a three-column matrix of coordinates 

